    "description": "A week from now, Handa Pilipinas will hold its final leg for the year in the Visayas, happening at the SMX Convention Center in Bacolod City, Negros Occidental from October 27-29, 2025. \n        This year’s Handa Pilipinas Visayas Leg marks another milestone in building a resilient and sustainable Philippines, co-hosted by the Provincial Government of Negros Occidental. \n        With the theme “Padayon Visayas: STI for a Resilient, United, and Sustainable Visayas,” the three-day event features interactive disaster preparedness exhibits and a conference highlighting science, technology, and innovation (STI) as tools for resilience. \n        The exhibits are open to the public, especially students eager to learn how STI helps communities prepare for disasters and adapt to climate change. Handa Pilipinas is a DOST national campaign promoting awareness, collaboration, and community resilience.",
